-- Herkules Defense Project Needs Additional $1.2 Billion, Handelsblatt Says
-- Ragnhild Kjetland
-- 2010-04-23T05:43:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-23/herkules-defense-project-needs-additional-1-2-billion-handelsblatt-says.html

          
          
             The German Defense Ministry’s
project to provide the army with a new communications
infrastructure needs another 918 million euros ($1.2 billion),
Handelsblatt reported, citing a ministry audit.  
 The project, known as “Herkules,” was set up with Siemens
AG and International Business Machines Corp. and was originally
projected to cost 6.8 billion euros, the newspaper said.  
 To contact the reporter on this story: Ragnhild Kjetland in
Frankfurt   rkjetland@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        